mages/2026/3/20/NCAA_First_and_Second.jpg"><media:title>NCAA WBB First and Second</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/20/NCAA_First_and_Second.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 20 Mar 2026 08:12:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>9</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58897</s:story_id></item><item><title>Watters Advances to Quarterfinals at NCAA Wrestling Championships</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/19/watters-advances-to-quarterfinals-at-ncaa-wrestling-championships</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/19/watters-advances-to-quarterfinals-at-ncaa-wrestling-championships</guid><category>Wrestling</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Ty Watters at 2026 NCAA Wrestling Championships" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/19/3I3A9671__1_.jpg" /><br /><br />CLEVELAND, Ohio – Redshirt sophomore Ty Watters of the West Virginia University wrestling team advanced to his second career quarterfinals at the 2026 NCAA Wrestling Championships at Rocket Arena in Cleveland on Thursday.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/19/3I3A9671__1_.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/19/3I3A9671__1_.jpg"><media:title>Ty Watters at 2026 NCAA Wrestling Championships</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/19/3I3A9671__1_.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 19 Mar 2026 22:54:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>18</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58896</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Win Series Opener Against BYU</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/19/baseball-mountaineers-win-series-opener-against-byu</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/19/baseball-mountaineers-win-series-opener-against-byu</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Dawson Montesa" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/19/EKQ01558.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 20 West Virginia University baseball team opened its series against BYU with a 7-4-win, Thursday evening at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 14-4 and 3-1 in Big 12 play while the Cougars fall to 10-10 and 2-2 in conference action.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/19/EKQ01558.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/19/EKQ01558.jpg"><media:title>Dawson Montesa</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/19/EKQ01558.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 19 Mar 2026 21:39:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58895</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Fall to No. 13 ASU</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/19/tennis-mountaineers-fall-to-no-13-asu</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/19/tennis-mountaineers-fall-to-no-13-asu</guid><category>Tennis</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Laura Morillo" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/19/GB707840.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University tennis team (6-8, 0-7 Big 12) fell to No. 13 Arizona State (12-4, 4-2 Big 12), 4-0, on Thursday afternoon at the Mountaineer Tennis Courts.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/19/GB707840.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/19/GB707840.jpg"><media:title>Laura Morillo</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/19/GB707840.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 19 Mar 2026 20:19:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>15</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58894</s:story_id></item><item><title>Bush Named Big 12 Scholar Athlete of the Year, First WVU Wrestler to Earn Award</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/19/wrestling-bush-named-big-12-scholar-athlete-of-the-year-first-wvu-wrestler-to-earn-award</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/19/wrestling-bush-named-big-12-scholar-athlete-of-the-year-first-wvu-wrestler-to-earn-award</guid><category>Wrestling</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Ian Bush at 2026 Big 12 Wrestling Championships" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/18/VTU01738.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Redshirt junior Ian Bush of the West Virginia University wrestling team has been named the Scholar Athlete of the Year for wrestling in the Big 12 Conference for the 2025-26 season.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/18/VTU01738.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/18/VTU01738.jpg"><media:title>Ian Bush at 2026 Big 12 Wrestling Championships</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/18/VTU01738.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 19 Mar 2026 16:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>18</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58893</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Open Outdoor Season with Split-Squad Weekend</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/19/track-field-mountaineers-open-outdoor-season-with-split-squad-weekend</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/19/track-field-mountaineers-open-outdoor-season-with-split-squad-weekend</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Audrey Thomas" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/19/JLS_5638.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University track and field team opens the outdoor season with a split-squad weekend on March 20-21. The Mountaineers will host the Marty Pushkin Invitational in Morgantown while another group travels to Tampa, Fla., to compete in the USF Alumni Invitational.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/19/JLS_5638.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/19/JLS_5638.jpg"><media:title>Audrey Thomas</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/19/JLS_5638.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 19 Mar 2026 12:35:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58892</s:story_id></item><item><title>Six Mountaineers Set to Compete at 2026 NCAA Wrestling Championships</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/18/six-mountaineers-set-to-compete-at-2026-ncaa-wrestling-championships</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/18/six-mountaineers-set-to-compete-at-2026-ncaa-wrestling-championships</guid><category>Wrestling</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Rocket Arena (2026 NCAA Wrestling Championships)" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/18/_YNX8064.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Six Mountaineers from the West Virginia University wrestling team are set to compete in the 2026 NCAA Wrestling Championships on March 19-21, at Rocket Arena in Cleveland.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/18/_YNX8064.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/18/_YNX8064.jpg"><media:title>Rocket Arena (2026 NCAA Wrestling Championships)</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/18/_YNX8064.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 18 Mar 2026 16:46:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>18</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58891</s:story_id></item></channel></rss>